{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 29,
  "title": "第二十九章（自然）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "將欲取天下而為之 吾見亓弗得已"
    },
    {
      "text": "夫天下 神器也 非可為者也"
    },
    {
      "text": "為者敗之 執者失之"
    },
    {
      "text": "物或行或隨 或炅或吹 或強或䂳 或培或橢"
    },
    {
      "text": "是以聖人去甚 去大 去楮"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 5,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "欲以有為治民。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "我見其不得天道人心已明矣，天道惡煩濁，人心惡多欲。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "器，物也。人乃天下之神物也，神物好安靜，不可以有為治。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "以有為治之，則敗其質性。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 5,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "強執教之，則失其情實，生於詐偽也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "上所行，下必隨之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "呴，溫也。吹，寒也。有所溫必有所寒也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "有所強大，必有所贏弱也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "載，安也。隳，危也。有所安必有所危，明人君不可以有為治國與治身也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "甚謂貪淫聲色。奢謂服飾飲食。泰謂宮室臺榭。去此三者，處中和，行無為，則天下自化。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "神，無形無方也。器，合成也。無形以合，故謂之神器也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "萬物以自然為性，故可因而不可為也。可通而不可執也。物有常性，而造為之，故必敗也。物有往來而執之，故必失矣。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 15
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "凡此諸或，言物事逆順反覆，不施為執割也。聖人達自然之至，暢萬物之情，故因而不為，順而不施。除其所以迷，去其所以惑，故心不亂而物性自得之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
